### VIEW MY RESUME
GET http://localhost:4000/api/resume/view

### DELETE MY RESUME
DELETE http://localhost:4000/api/resume/delete

### SAVE RESUME DATA
POST http://localhost:4000/api/resume/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "resumeUrl": "https://res.cloudinary.com/demo/image/upload/sample.pdf",
    "resumeData": {
        "skills": [
            "JavaScript",
            "React",
            "Node.js"
        ],
        "experience": [],
        "projects": [
            {
                "title": "Smart Placement Tracker",
                "description": "A fullstack placement tracker.",
                "github": "https://github.com/...",
                "link": "",
                "technologies": ["React", "Node.js"]
            }
        ],
        "education": []
    },
    "atsScore": 85
}

### UPLOAD RESUME
# Note: Testing file uploads in .http files is tricky. 
# You need a real PDF file named "sample.pdf" in this same directory for this to work.
# It's usually easier to test the upload route from the frontend UI!
POST http://localhost:4000/api/resume/upload

